comments.body:
Thanks for reaching out @sebastienhasa!

As you mentioned, auto-updates are currently heavily tied to systemd. While we are planning to implement simple rollbacks in the near future, there are no plans to move away from systemd. But nothing is carved into stone yet which is also why we marked the auto-update command as experimental.

@mheon @baude, as many things have changed in the backend, I want to give the idea another shot. With the new code, how far are we from being able to recreate a container from an existing one?
